GetStack.name: GetStack
GetStack.documentation: Returns information about the specified stack. You can get a list of stack IDs by calling ListStackSummaries.

GetSubnet.name: GetSubnet
GetSubnet.documentation: Returns information about the specified subnet. You can get a list of subnets associated with a particular VPC by calling GetVpc.

GetVpc.name: GetVpc
GetVpc.documentation: Returns information about the specified VPC. You can get a list of VPCs by calling ListVpcSummaries.

ListAmis.name: ListAmis
ListAmis.documentation: Returns information about the Amazon Machine Images (AMIs) associated with the specified VPC. Optionally, you can specify a filter to narrow the results to Windows AMIs only.

ListStackSummaries.name: ListStackSummaries
ListStackSummaries.documentation: Returns summary information about stacks in the current account. Optionally, you can specify filters to narrow the results. Use the returned StackId with GetStack to get more information about a particular stack.

ListSubnetSummaries.name: ListSubnetSummaries
ListSubnetSummaries.documentation: Returns summary information about subnets in the current account. Optionally, you can specify filters to narrow the results. Use the returned SubnetId with the GetSubnet operation to get more information about a particular subnet.

ListVpcSummaries.name: ListVpcSummaries
ListVpcSummaries.documentation: Returns summary information about available VPCs. Optionally, you can specify filters to narrow the results. Use a VpcId with GetVpc to get more information about a particular VPC.

AmiType.documentation: The type of the instance (for example, t2.micro).

Architecture.documentation: The architecture of the instance (i386 or x86_64).

BlockDeviceMappings.documentation: The block device mappings for the instance.

CreationTime.documentation: The date and time that the AMI was created.

Platform.documentation: The platform of the AMI: "windows" if the instance OS is Microsoft Windows Server; otherwise, blank.

RamdiskId.documentation: The RAM disk ID of the instance.

RootDeviceName.documentation: The name of the root device (for example, /dev/sda1 or /dev/xvda).

RootDeviceType.documentation: The type of the root device (ebs or instance-store).

Ami.documentation: Information about an Amazon Machine Image (AMI), which is a template for a software configuration (for example, an operating system, an application server, and applications).

Ebs.documentation: Specifications for an Amazon Elastic Block Store (Amazon EBS) volume.

NoDevice.documentation: When present, unmaps a device that is defined in the AMI.

VirtualName.documentation: The name of the virtual device. For example, "ephemeral0".

BlockDeviceMapping.documentation: An AWS CloudFormation block device mapping description. For more information, see Amazon EC2 Block Device Mapping Property in the AWS CloudFormation user guide.

DeleteOnTermination.documentation: Indicates whether the volume should be deleted after it is terminated.

Iops.documentation: The number of I/O operations per second (IOPS) that the volume supports.

SnapshotId.documentation: The snapshot ID of the volume to use to create the block device.

VolumeType.documentation: The volume type. You can specify standard, io1, or gp2. If you set the type to io1, you must also set the Iops property.

EbsBlockDevice.documentation: Specifies the characteristics of an Amazon Elastic Block Store (Amazon EBS) volume. For more information, see Amazon Elastic Block Store Block Device Property in the AWS CloudFormation user guide.

Key.documentation: The key of a stack output item.

Value.documentation: The value of a stack output item.

Output.documentation: A key/value pair this is returned when a Stack is created.

Parameter.documentation: A key/value pair that specifies a parameter name and value when creating a Stack.

ResourceNotFoundException.documentation: The specified resource cannot be found. Actual status code: 404

CreatedTime.documentation: The date and time that the stack was created.

Outputs.documentation: The outputs from the creation of the stack.

Parameters.documentation: The parameters that were used to create the stack.

Status.documentation: The status of the stack. Possible values: CreateCompleted | CreateInProgress | CreateFailed | UpdateCompleted | UpdateInProgress | RollbackCompleted | RollbackInProgress | RollbackFailed | DeleteCompleted | DeleteInProgress | DeleteFailed | Unknown

Tags.documentation: One or more user-defined key/value pairs associated with the stack.

VpcId.documentation: The ID of the VPC associated with the stack.

Stack.documentation: Information about a stack, which is one or more infrastructure components that have been instantiated in response to a request for change (RFC).

CreatedTime.documentation: The date and time that the stack was created.

StackTemplateId.documentation: The ID of the stack template that was used to create the stack.

VpcId.documentation: The ID of the VPC, in the form vpc-a1b2c3d4e5f67890e of the stack.

StackSummary.documentation: Summary information about a stack, which is one or more infrastructure components that have been instantiated in response to a request for change (RFC).

AvailableIpAddressCount.documentation: The number of IP addresses supported by the subnet.

LastModifiedTime.documentation: The date and time that the subnet was most recently modified.

Tag.documentation: A key/value pair associated with a resource.

VpcId.documentation: The ID of the VPC, in the form vpc-a1b2c3d4.

documentation:
AWS Managed Services SKMS

You can use the SKMS API to get information about:

  • AMIs (ListAmis)

  • Stacks (ListStackSummaries and GetStack)

  • Subnets (ListSubnetSummaries and GetSubnet)

  • VPCs (ListVpcSummaries and GetVpc)

For more information and examples, see Service Knowledge Management in the AWS Managed Services User Guide.

Service Endpoint

The HTTP endpoint for the SKMS API is:

  • https://amsskms.us-east-1.amazonaws.com
